					<span class="label"><a name="footnote25-10405_000_030">25.</a></span>
					<p>The spirit is in the likeness of the person (see <a href="http://www.lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/77.2?lang=eng#1" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Doctrine and Covenants 77:2</a>).</p>
				</li>
				<li class="footnote " id="-10405_000_030"><a name="-10405_000_030">&nbsp;</a>
					<span class="label"><a name="footnote26-10405_000_030">26.</a></span>
					<p>See <a href="http://www.lds.org/scriptures/bofm/3-ne/14.9-11?lang=eng#8" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">3&nbsp;Nephi 14:9&ndash;11</a>.</p>
				</li>
				<li class="footnote " id="-10405_000_030"><a name="-10405_000_030">&nbsp;</a>
					<span class="label"><a name="footnote27-10405_000_030">27.</a></span>
					<p>The spirit, not the body, is the active, responsible component of the soul. Without the spirit, the body is dead (see <a href="http://www.lds.org/scriptures/nt/james/2.26?lang=eng#25" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">James 2:26</a>). It is the spirit, therefore, that chooses good or evil and will be held accountable for both the positive and negative attributes it possesses at the Final Judgment (see <a href="http://www.lds.org/scriptures/bofm/alma/41.3-7?lang=eng#2" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Alma 41:3&ndash;7</a>).</p>
				</li>
				<li class="footnote " id="-10405_000_030"><a name="-10405_000_030">&nbsp;</a>
					<span class="label"><a name="footnote28-10405_000_030">28.</a></span>
					<p>Spiritual attributes also include &ldquo;faith, virtue, knowledge, temperance, patience, brotherly kindness, godliness, charity, humility, [and] diligence&rdquo; (<a href="http://www.lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/4.6?lang=eng#5" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Doctrine and Covenants 4:6</a>).</p>
				</li>
				<li class="footnote " id="-10405_000_030"><a name="-10405_000_030">&nbsp;</a>
					<span class="label"><a name="footnote29-10405_000_030">29.</a></span>
					<p>See <a href="http://www.lds.org/scriptures/bofm/2-ne/2.11-16,21-26?lang=eng#10" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">2&nbsp;Nephi 2:11&ndash;16, 21&ndash;26</a>; <a href="http://www.lds.org/scriptures/bofm/moro/10.33-34?lang=eng#32" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Moroni 10:33&ndash;34</a>.</p>
				</li>
				<li class="footnote " id="-10405_000_030"><a name="-10405_000_030">&nbsp;</a>
					<span class="label"><a name="footnote30-10405_000_030">30.</a></span>
					<p>This is the doctrine of Christ (see <a href="http://www.lds.org/scriptures/bofm/2-ne/31.11-21?lang=eng#10" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">2&nbsp;Nephi 31:11&ndash;21</a>).</p>
				</li>
				<li class="footnote " id="-10405_000_030"><a name="-10405_000_030">&nbsp;</a>
					<span class="label"><a name="footnote31-10405_000_030">31.</a></span>
					<p><a href="http://www.lds.org/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/15.28?lang=eng#27" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Mosiah 15:28</a>; see also <a href="http://www.lds.org/scriptures/bofm/1-ne/19.17?lang=eng#16" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">1&nbsp;Nephi 19:17</a>; <a href="http://www.lds.org/scriptures/bofm/2-ne/26.13?lang=eng#12" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">2&nbsp;Nephi 26:13</a>; <a href="http://www.lds.org/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/3.20?lang=eng#19" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Mosiah 3:20</a>; <a href="http://www.lds.org/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/15.28?lang=eng#27" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">15:28</a>; <a href="http://www.lds.org/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/16.1?lang=eng#0" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">16:1</a>; <a href="http://www.lds.org/scriptures/bofm/alma/37.4?lang=eng#3" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Alma 37:4</a>; <a href="http://www.lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/1.18-23?lang=eng#17" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Doctrine and Covenants 1:18&ndash;23</a>; <a href="http://www.lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/77.11?lang=eng#10" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">77:11</a>; <a href="http://www.lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/133.37?lang=eng#36" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">133:37</a>.</p>
				</li>
				<li class="footnote " id="-10405_000_030"><a name="-10405_000_030">&nbsp;</a>
					<span class="label"><a name="footnote32-10405_000_030">32.</a></span>
					<p><a href="http://www.lds.org/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/4.9-10?lang=eng#8" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Mosiah 4:9&ndash;10</a>.</p>
				</li>
				<li class="footnote " id="-10405_000_030"><a name="-10405_000_030">&nbsp;</a>
					<span class="label"><a name="footnote33-10405_000_030">33.</a></span>
					<p>&ldquo;Eternal life &hellip; is the greatest of all the gifts of God&rdquo; (<a href="http://www.lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/14.7?lang=eng#6" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Doctrine and Covenants 14:7</a>).</p>
				</li>
			</ol>
                                        
